Perfect! I've successfully read all the requested files. Here's a comprehensive report on the channel plugin structure based on the IRC and Nostr implementations.

## Channel Plugin Structure Report

### 1. Package Configuration (`package.json`)

**IRC Example:**
```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/irc",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw IRC channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "install": {
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    },
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "irc",
      "label": "IRC",
      "selectionLabel": "IRC (Server + Nick)",
      "detailLabel": "IRC",
      "docsPath": "/channels/irc",
      "docsLabel": "irc",
      "blurb": "classic IRC networks with DM/channel routing and pairing controls.",
      "aliases": ["internet-relay-chat"],
      "systemImage": "network"
    }
  }
}
```

**Nostr Example:** Adds npm dependencies and install/release configuration:
```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "nostr-tools": "^2.23.3"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/nostr",
      "defaultChoice": "npm",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    },
    "release": {
      "publishToNpm": true
    }
  }
}
```

**Telegram Example:** More complex with dependencies and markdown capability:
```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "@grammyjs/runner": "^2.0.3",
    "grammy": "^1.41.1"
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "channel": {
      "markdownCapable": true,
      "selectionExtras": ["https://openclaw.ai"],
      "bundle": {
        "stageRuntimeDependencies": true
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 2. Plugin Manifest (`openclaw.plugin.json`)

Simple config schema structure for all plugins:
```json
{
  "id": "irc",
  "channels": ["irc"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

The `id`, `channels` array, and empty `configSchema` appear consistent across IRC and Nostr.

### 3. Main Entry Point (`index.ts`)

**IRC:**
```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { ircPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setIrcRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

